        <nav>
         <button><a href="#company-research">Company Research</a></button>
         <button><a href="#behavioral-questions">Behavioral Questions</a></button>
         <button><a href="#technical-questions">Technical Questions</a></button>
        <button><a href="#questions-to-ask">Questions to Ask</a></button>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <div id="company-research">
            <h2>1. Company Research</h2>
            <p>Before any interview, it's crucial to research the company. This shows genuine interest and helps you tailor your answers.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Mission & Values:</strong> What drives the company?</li>
                <li><strong>Recent News:</strong> Any new products, funding, or major announcements?</li>
                <li><strong>The Team:</strong> Who are the key people you'll be meeting?</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div id="behavioral-questions">
            <h2>2. Behavioral Questions</h2>
            <p>These questions assess your past behavior to predict future performance. Use the <strong>STAR method</strong> (Situation, Task, Action, Result).</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Tell me about a time you failed.</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Describe a challenging project you worked on.</strong></li>
                <li><strong>How do you handle conflict with a coworker?</strong></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div id="technical-questions">
            <h2>3. Technical Questions</h2>
            <p>Specific to the role, these questions test your knowledge and problem-solving skills.</p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <h3>HTML & CSS</h3>
                <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;My Page&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
                </code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block">
                <h3>JavaScript</h3>
                <pre><code>function greet(name) {
  return Hello, ${name}!;
}
console.log(greet("Interviewer"));
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="questions-to-ask">
            <h2>4. Questions to Ask the Interviewer</h2>
            <p>Asking thoughtful questions shows you're engaged and serious about the opportunity. Always have a few ready.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>What does a typical day look like in this role?</li>
                <li>What are the team's biggest challenges right now?</li>
                <li>How is success measured in this position?</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </main>

